50 hours In Amsterdam – A Whirlwind Experience In The Venice Of The North

@adamlookout @stroopperie @mannekenfriet 

Last Slide — The RedLight Area In Amsterdam is electric !!!

✅ Pros

- Safe & Walkable
- Great Public Transport
- Safe Nightlife

⚠️ Cons

- Popular spots can be extremely crowded. Pickpocketing isn’t rampant, but always stay aware, especially in busy areas

- While it’s safe to walk through the Red Light District, it may feel uncomfortable for some female travellers

- Weather Mood Swings

- Be alert when walking—cyclists won’t always stop for pedestrians.

If You’re Planning A Short Getaway, Amsterdam Is The Perfect Blend Of Charm, Modern-Day/Night Vibrance – All Wrapped Into A Compact, Walkable City.

latestPosts.caption:
Paris Broke My Heart In The Worst Way 💔 

My recent experience left me shocked, scared, and deeply disappointed.

➡️ Lack of Safety:
There’s little to no visible police or security presence — not at train stations, not near monuments, not even in crowded public areas.
I was eve-teased by 6-7 boys and felt completely helpless. The fear of “what if they hurt me?” haunted me the entire time even now. 

➡️ Snatching & Theft:
Pickpocketing and snatching are rampant. My taxi driver even told me about his friend getting stabbed just for refusing to hand over his belongings. Imagine hearing that as a tourist.

➡️ No Support System:
When I sought help or clarification — even from train officials — I was misled. I ended up being sent 45 minutes outside Paris by someone who was supposed to assist me. There’s no accountability, no tourist-friendly environment.

➡️ Unwelcoming Locals:
Even when they know English, many locals choose not to help. The coldness and superiority complex is real — and painful when you’re already feeling lost.

⸻

I’m sharing this not to spread fear, but to share facts.
So many women and solo travelers go unspoken about their bad experiences — we only see curated, romanticized Paris content. But behind the Eiffel Tower lights, there’s another side — one that deserves attention.

Be cautious. Be aware. And please — prioritize your safety over the hype.

🙏 Forever Grateful To My Guru ji & The Universe For Protecting Me.

Nature’s Calm In The Fjords, City’s Soul In The Streets — Oslo, You Balance It All So Beautifully 🌊🎈🇳🇴 #constitutionday 

—— Last Photo Is My Favourite ☘️🌸

✅ Pros

- Extremely Safe for Women
- Progressive & Respectful Culture
- Clean, Organized, and Easy to Navigate
- Oslo is surrounded by forests, fjords, and lakes. As a female traveler, you can enjoy solo hikes or serene moments in nature without venturing far from the city.
- Language & Communication

⚠️ Cons

- Oslo is one of the most expensive cities in Europe
- Quiet Nightlife
- Cold Weather & Windy
- Reserved Social Culture
- Limited Shopping or Fashion Culture
